00w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Sick-Of-It-All-Mobb-Deep@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Sick-Of-It-All-Mobb-Deep@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Sick-Of-It-All-Mobb-Deep@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Sick-Of-It-All-Mobb-Deep@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sick-of-it-all">Sick Of It All</a>已针对<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/mobb-deep">Mobb Deep</a>最近与 Supreme 的合作提起诉讼，涉嫌侵犯其商标标识。</p><p>该问题与纽约硬核乐队的标志“Alleyway Crew Dragon”有关，该标志是乐队成员于 1987 年（乐队成立一年后）推出的，此后一直在他们的唱片、商品和广告中使用。</p><p>该诉讼于上周三（10 月 11 日）提起，将 Mobb Deep 的 Havoc (Kejuan Muchita)、已故说唱歌手 Prodigy (Albert Johnson) 的遗产以及 Supreme 的所有者 Chapter 4 Corp 列为被告。</p><p>去年夏天，街头服饰品牌 Supreme 与嘻哈二人组 Mobb Deep 推出了合作款，其中包括在衬衫、帽子和其他服装上印有龙标志的单品。</p><p>根据<a href="https://www.stereogum.com/2239304/sick-of-it-all-sue-mobb-deep-over-supreme-collab/news/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Stereogum</em></a>的一份报告，这些文件称“这些案件是由于被告不当和非法使用与原告固有的独特、无可争议的著名标志几乎相同的标志而引起的”。 </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/CtrnjHSOBKn/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:16px;"><div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;"></div><div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;"><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;"></div><div style=" backgrou